{
 "name": "RPlog_Jessalyn_s_Hardest_Lesson",
 "title": "Jessalyn's Hardest Lesson",
 "summary": "Aboard the Millennium Falcon, Jessalyn Valios comes to brief Luke Skywalker, first sharing her discovery that a creature on Myrkr makes the Force nearly impossible to sense, then steeling herself to explain her failed attempt to save Simon Sezirok from the dark side. Luke gently reassures her that caring for the fallen may yet anchor him to the Light, but the conversation turns painful as Jessalyn confronts the Jedi Master about his own guarded heart, his two-year absence while she was captive of Valak, and the love for him she has never been able to set aside. When Luke offers only careful warmth and the safety of the present, Jessalyn finally resolves to let him go, declaring it his loss this time before marching out -- leaving a confused Luke to reflect that she will need time.",
